==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Handwriting
<hw>Hand"writ`ing</hw> <pr>(-r⟦imac⟧t"⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The cast or form of writing peculiar to each hand or
person; chirography.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is written by hand; manuscript.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>The handwriting on the wall</b></col>, <cd>a doom
pronounced; an omen of disaster.</cd> <rj><au>Dan. v.
5.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hand-written</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>handwritten</ent>⟦br⟧
